04/06/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said on Thursday (3 June) that the government has proposed providing treatment to Iraqi children in Croatian hospitals. The proposal was well received by US officials, he added. According to the prime minister, discussions are also under way about training Iraqi forensic experts in Croatia, as part of Zagreb's effort to participate in the post-war reconstruction of Iraq. (Vecrenji List - 04/06/04; HINA - 03/06/04)
